data.name: lblInstructions.Text
data.value:
In the textbox provided, create or copy & paste a SQL statement that will be used to display data in an inquiry grid.
It is recommended that the SQL statement be developed in a tool such as SQL Server Management Studio or similar to provide a well-formatted, proper and working SQL statement.
The Inquiry Engine will create a wrapper for the SQL statement based upon the columns returned by the SQL statement. Note: These columns are manually specified in the exact order of the return columns of the SQL statement in the wizard as the wizard does not parse or validate the format or content of the SQL statement.
The Inquiry Engine will apply the supplied 'where clause' to the generated wrapper if a 'where clause' is supplied. This 'where clause' is applied to the wrapper and is considered the 'first-level' sort or filter. It is separate from any 'where clauses' used in the SQL statement itself. The 'WHERE' key word will not be specified in the wizard field (i.e. IDCUST = {0} not WHERE IDCUST = {0}).
The Inquiry Engine will apply the required 'order by clause' to the generated wrapper. This 'order by clause' is applied to the wrapper. It is separate from any 'order by clauses' used in the SQL statement itself. The 'ORDER BY' key word will not be specified in the wizard field (i.e. IDCUST not ORDER BY IDCUST).
The examples on the following tabs show various SQL statements (with their wrappers, where and order by clauses already applied). But, remmeber that the SQL statement provided will NOT include the wrapper, the 'where clause' or the 'order by clause'. The SQL statement example provide the ability to understand the proper format required by the wizard.

data.name: txtExample1.Text
data.value: SELECT [ITEMNO], [DESC], [PRICEBY], [PRICELIST], [CURRENCY], [BPRICETYPE], [DBASEPRICE], [DBASEUNIT], [SPRICETYPE], [DSALEPRICE], [DSALEUNIT], [CONTRACTPRICING] FROM (SELECT C.IDCUST, I.ITEMNO, I.[DESC], D.PRICELIST, D.PRICEBY, D.BPRICETYPE, D.SPRICETYPE, D.CURRENCY, --D.BP as 'DBASEPRICE', --D.BU as 'DBASEUNIT', --D.SP as 'DSALEPRICE', --D.SU as 'DSALEUNIT', case when D.BPRICETYPE = 1 then D.BP else null end as 'DBASEPRICE', case when D.BPRICETYPE = 1 then D.BU else null end as 'DBASEUNIT', case when D.SPRICETYPE = 1 then D.SP else null end as 'DSALEPRICE', case when D.SPRICETYPE = 1 then D.SU else null end as 'DSALEUNIT', case when PR.PRICELIST IS NULL then 0 else 1 end as 'CONTRACTPRICING' FROM ICITEM I JOIN ( SELECT ITEMNO, CURRENCY, PRICELIST, PRICEBY, BPRICETYPE, max(BU) as BU, max(BP) as BP, SPRICETYPE, max(SU) as SU, max(SP) as SP FROM (SELECT P.ITEMNO, P.CURRENCY, P.PRICELIST, P.PRICEBY, P.BPRICETYPE, P.SPRICETYPE, case when PD.DPRICETYPE = 1 then PD.QTYUNIT else null end as 'BU', case when PD.DPRICETYPE = 1 then PD.UNITPRICE else null end as 'BP', case when PD.DPRICETYPE = 2 then PD.QTYUNIT else null end as 'SU', case when PD.DPRICETYPE = 2 then PD.UNITPRICE else null end as 'SP' FROM ICPRIC P LEFT JOIN ICPRICP PD on P.ITEMNO = PD.ITEMNO and PD.PRICELIST = P.PRICELIST and PD.CURRENCY = P.CURRENCY ) a GROUP BY ITEMNO, CURRENCY, PRICELIST, PRICEBY, BPRICETYPE, SPRICETYPE ) D on I.ITEMNO = D.ITEMNO JOIN ARCUS C on C.PRICLIST = D.PRICELIST and C.CODECURN = D.CURRENCY LEFT JOIN ICCUPR PR on C.IDCUST = PR.CUSTNO and I.ITEMNO = PR.ITEMNO and C.PRICLIST = PR.PRICELIST and C.PRICLIST = D.PRICELIST ) wrapper WHERE IDCUST = '{0}' ORDER BY ITEMNO
